# Technical Documentation

## Overview

This project models MRTA as a combinatorial optimization problem.

We use tensor-network-inspired quantum circuits (via quimb) to encode structure.

## V1

- Exact brute-force solver
- Baseline correctness model
- Tensor network used only for representation

## V2

- Introduces energy function:
  - Classical cost
  - Constraint penalty
  - Nonlinear tensor modulation
- Still uses exact search

## V3

- Scales to N robots/tasks
- Uses simulated annealing
- Approximate optimization method
- Measures runtime performance

## Tensor Network Role

Tensor networks encode MRTA structure using:
- Hadamard gates
- Rotation gates (RY)

Library: quimb
